The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 13: Sebi has asked the government to clarify whether takeover of Indian companies by foreign investors under the automatic route complies with its objective of rationalising the FDI policy, minister of state for finance Pawan Bansal informed the Rajya Sabha. The government had rationalised the policy of allowing FDI under automatic route early last year.

 New Delhi, March 13: The Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC) has received Rs 864 crore in final settlement of an insurance claim for the oil facility at Mumbai High that was gutted in a fire in July 2005.

 New Delhi, March 13: The Manpower employment outlook survey for the second quarter of 2007 released today shows that the job market in India will continue to grow, but at a slower pace than the previous year. 

 Mumbai, March 13: Geojit Financial Services today issued 5.68 crore shares and 2.28 crore warrants to BNP Paribas, making the company its single largest shareholder. The Re 1 face value shares have been allotted to BNP Paribas at Rs 26 per share.

 New Delhi, March 13: With an aim to increase trade between India and China, express visas, launched today by Assocham and the Embassy of China, will be issued to Indian businessmen recommended by the India-China Business Alliance (ICBA).




